In [14]:
fig,axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))
fig.suptitle("Total Profit Vs Sales")
sns.barplot(data=df_ss.groupby('Sub-Category')['Sales','Profit'].agg(sum),x='Sales',y='Profit',ax=axes[1])
df_ss.groupby('Sub-Category')['Sales','Profit'].agg(sum).plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[0])
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()
In [15]:
fig,axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))
fig.suptitle("Total Sales Vs Quantity")
sns.barplot(data=df_ss.groupby('Sub-Category')['Sales','Quantity'].agg(sum),x='Sales',y='Quantity',ax=axes[1])
df_ss.groupby('Sub-Category')['Sales','Quantity'].agg(sum).plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[0])
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.show()

fig,axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(14,5))

df_ss.groupby('Sub-Category')['Profit','Discount'].agg(sum).plot(kind='bar',ax=axes[1]).set_title('Profit & Discount Relation based on sub-category')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)

fig,axes = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(16,8))

sns.distplot(df_ss['Quantity'],ax=axes[1,1])
plt.show()

fig,axes = plt.subplots(2,2,figsize=(16,8))
fig.suptitle("Sales with different shipping modes and Segments",fontsize=16)
sns.barplot(df_ss['Ship Mode'],df_ss['Sales'],ax=axes[0,0])
sns.lineplot(df_ss['Ship Mode'],df_ss['Sales'],ax=axes[0,1])
sns.barplot(df_ss['Segment'],df_ss['Sales'],ax=axes[1,0])
sns.lineplot(df_ss['Segment'],df_ss['Sales'],ax=axes[1,1])
plt.show()

Comment:-¶

1) The features Profit and Discount are highly related.

2) Over Less quantity of products also the sales were high.

3) The maximum Quantity of product in demand in range 2-4.

4) The mode of shipping doesn't affect much to the sales.

5) The Home Office provides highest sales followed by Corporateby a slight variation.
